  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Emergence agitation is a frequent complication that can have serious consequences during
      recovery from general anesthesia. However, agitation has been poorly investigated in patients
      after craniotomy. In this prospective multicenter cohort study, adult patients will be
      enrolled after craniotomy and emergence agitation will be evaluated. The incidence, risk
      factors and outcome will be investigated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
